sentences: Claude Barthélemy (born August 22, 1956) is a French jazz guitarist.
He began playing with Michel Portal's ensemble Unit in 1978 and worked with Aldo Romano, Stu Martin, and Gérard Marais.
He co-founded the group Zhivaro in 1987 and from 1989 to 1991 was the director of Orchestre National de Jazz.

In the 1990s he led the octet La Nouvelle-Orleans, the quartet Monsieur Claude, and accompanied Elise Caron and Sylvie Cobo.

He assembled a trio with Jacques Mahieux and Jean-Luc Ponthieux in the early 1980s, in addition to working with Jean-Marc Padovani and Nouvel Orchestra Philharmonique.
